title: R Ladies Meet and Greet
description: Hello R enthusiasts! We are hosting a meet and greet for those interested at Puritan! Come whenever you want, leave whenever you want. Bring a project, a question, a friend! We can't wait to meet everyone.

title: R Ladies Meeting # 2
description: Meet us in Memorial 314 on the University of Arkansas Campus

title: First R-Ladies Event
description:
A first meeting for the Fayetteville Arkansas R Ladies.

Hopefully a time to meet, greet, and talk about some R basics.

The meeting location is in Memorial Hall of the UARK campus. The meeting will be in room 242

title: Data Cleaning with Alexandria Choate
description:
Meet us on zoom for a data cleaning webinar in R with Allie Choate a Doctoral Student of Clinical Psychology at the University of South Florida. She'll talk us through data cleaning with tricky data from Qualtrics in mind.

Learn more about Allie here: https://alliechoate.netlify.app/about/

title: [WEBINAR] Stephanie Long on Animated Graphics in R
description:
Join us as Stephanie Long reviews the steps she took to create an animated graphic.

Access the code for the workshop on our github: https://github.com/R-Ladies-Fayetteville-AR/GGAnimate-Demo

Meeting number (access code): 803 529 198

Meeting password: rladies57

Host key: 356267

title: Cari Bogulski on Data Cleaning and Alt-Academic Career Paths
description:
THIS EVENT WILL NOW BE AN ONLINE EVENT FOLLOWING THE CLOSING OF THE BREWER HUB IN LIGHT OF COVID 19.

Here is the link to tomorrow's (3/17) R-ladies WebEx remote meeting at 12:15pm:
https://uark.webex.com/uark/j.php?MTID=mc1aaf5d59905560ee0e0bcb5b3c4f14f

We hope you all can join! When you join the meeting please mute your audio and ask questions via the chat box.

Cari is very happy to present on data cleaning and some of what she does. In particular, she will talk about program evaluation as an interesting alt-ac possibility that she hadn't heard of when she was in graduate school.

title: Kayce Hyde talks through Data Imputation
Arkansas Center for Data Science Recruiter to Provide Webinar
description:
I’m so excited to announce that on Friday the 31st at 3PM, Katie Frazier, a recruiter for the Arkansas Center for Data Science (ACDS) will provide a **FREE** webinar to talk about the mission of ACDS.

She will discuss the following topics:

ACDS purpose
What is an apprenticeship?
Apprenticeships in Arkansas
What do we look for?
What is our interview process?
What companies do we work with?
Tips for applications/resumes

Please join this webinar by link : https://zoom.us/j/2089095106?pwd=Nk95MW9JeklBMjdLa3VMNE5lcjAwZz09

We hope to see many familiar names and hear some amazing questions for Katie! Please share this widely and freely if you know someone who might be interested in the opportunities that ACDS has.

title: Static Web Scraping for Researchers 2nd Session **Free Online Event**
description:
Presented By: Austin Wilkins
Workshop Description

This is for the 2nd session of this workshop.

Part one of this workshop will cover the basics surrounding scraping data from static webpages for research purposes. This will cover finding and selecting data, formatting a simple web scrape in R using the Rvest library.

Topic: Austin Wilkins' Zoom Meeting
Time: Jan 26, 2021 06:00 PM Central Time (US and Canada)

Join Zoom Meeting
https://us04web.zoom.us/j/7139079746?pwd=OTZ6dGZmeHRvK29tNVV6dUE2N3JTdz09

Meeting ID: 713 907 9746
Passcode: 6EpAVD

Learning Objectives (3 max):
• Learn to use R and Rvest to scrape static web pages.
• Understand how data is presented in HTML and how it can be gathered.
• Learn and understand the potential for gathering data using R.

title: R Ladies NWA Social Event
description:
This meeting is meant to be a way for R-Ladies NWA members and others to get together and meet. This meeting is meant to serve as a community organizing event R Ladies event for the coming year. We want to know how R Ladies NWA can help support your R journey.

This event will be hosted on Zoom! Link to come.
